    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required gradation level. The single gap (Test conditions, achieved level 1 vs. required level 2) is mitigated by cross-laboratory consistency and conservative acceptance bounds. The E/uval metric is satisfied for all three QoIs across all ensemble members. The credibility evidence is sufficient to support the intended regulatory use of the FEA model for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending. Package is filed under ProfileMinimal; digital signature is pending completion of the institutional signature workflow and will be appended prior to final regulatory submission.",
